What you need to know:

Kenya lost their opening match 69-51 to group B leaders Senegal while Mozambique despite bringing into the squad five new players went down heavily 91-68 to the Angolans who are second in the groupKenya head coach Elizabeth Mills is wary of the threat posed by the Mozambicans and has asked her charges to remain focused throughout the encounterAccording to Mills, the new players in the squad will definitely add a new dynamic and energy but she says Morans have prepared well to qualify for Afrobasket